Document: OptionButton
Path: godot/classes/class_optionbutton.rst
Summary: This chunk describes the item_focused and item_selected signals of the OptionButton class, detailing when they are emitted and their parameters.

Signals
Signal: item_focused(index: int)
Emitted when the user navigates to an item using the ProjectSettings.input/ui_up or ProjectSettings.input/ui_down input actions. The index of the item selected is passed as argument.

Signal: item_selected(index: int)
Emitted when the current item has been changed by the user. The index of the item selected is passed as argument.
allow_reselect must be enabled to reselect an item.
---CHUNK---
Document: OptionButton
Path: godot/classes/class_optionbutton.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for the OptionButton node, including item selection, search bar behavior, sizing, and individual item attributes.

Properties:
*   allow_reselect (bool): If true, the currently selected item can be selected again. Default: false.
    *   Method: set_allow_reselect(value: bool)
    *   Method: get_allow_reselect()
*   enable_search_bar_on_item_count (int): Enables the PopupMenu search bar if the item count is greater than 0. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_search_bar_enabled_on_item_count(value: int)
    *   Method: get_search_bar_enabled_on_item_count()
*   fit_to_longest_item (bool): If true, minimum size will be determined by the longest item's text, instead of the currently selected one's. Note: For performance reasons, the minimum size doesn't update immediately when adding, removing or modifying items. Default: true.
    *   Method: set_fit_to_longest_item(value: bool)
    *   Method: is_fit_to_longest_item()
*   item_count (int): The number of items to select from. Default: 0.
    *   Method: set_item_count(value: int)
    *   Method: get_item_count()
*   popup/item_{index}/disabled (bool): If true, the item at index is disabled. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range. Default: false.
*   popup/item_{index}/icon (Texture2D): The icon of the item at index. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range.
*   popup/item_{index}/id (int): The ID of the item at index. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range. Default: 0.
*   popup/item_{index}/separator (bool): If true, the item at index is a separator. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range. Default: false.
*   popup/item_{index}/text (String): The text of the item at index. Note: index is a value in the 0 .. item_count - 1 range. Default: "".
*   selected (int): The index of the currently selected item, or -1 if no item is selected. Default: -1.
    *   Method: get_selected()
---CHUNK---
Document: OptionButton
Path: godot/classes/class_optionbutton.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for adding, removing, querying, and modifying items within an OptionButton, as well as managing its popup and selection state.

Method: add_icon_item(texture: Texture2D, label: String, id: int = -1)
Adds an item, with a texture icon, text label and (optionally) id. If no id is passed, the item index will be used as the item's ID. New items are appended at the end. Note: The item will be selected if there are no other items.

Method: add_item(label: String, id: int = -1)
Adds an item, with text label and (optionally) id. If no id is passed, the item index will be used as the item's ID. New items are appended at the end. Note: The item will be selected if there are no other items.

Method: add_separator(text: String = "")
Adds a separator to the list of items. Separators help to group items, and can optionally be given a text header. A separator also gets an index assigned, and is appended at the end of the item list.

Method: clear()
Clears all the items in the OptionButton.

Method: get_item_auto_translate_mode(idx: int) -> AutoTranslateMode
Returns the auto translate mode of the item at index idx.

Method: get_item_icon(idx: int) -> Texture2D
Returns the icon of the item at index idx.

Method: get_item_id(idx: int) -> int
Returns the ID of the item at index idx.

Method: get_item_index(id: int) -> int
Returns the index of the item with the given id.

Method: get_item_metadata(idx: int) -> Variant
Retrieves the metadata of an item. Metadata may be any type and can be used to store extra information about an item, such as an external string ID.

Method: get_item_text(idx: int) -> String
Returns the text of the item at index idx.

Method: get_item_tooltip(idx: int) -> String
Returns the tooltip of the item at index idx.

Method: get_popup() -> PopupMenu
Returns the PopupMenu contained in this button. Warning: This is a required internal node, removing and freeing it may cause a crash. If you wish to hide it or any of its children, use their Window.visible property.

Method: get_selectable_item(from_last: bool = false) -> int
Returns the index of the first item which is not disabled, or marked as a separator. If from_last is true, the items will be searched in reverse order. Returns -1 if no item is found.

Method: get_selected_id() -> int
Returns the ID of the selected item, or -1 if no item is selected.

Method: get_selected_metadata() -> Variant
Gets the metadata of the selected item. Metadata for items can be set using set_item_metadata().

Method: has_selectable_items() -> bool
Returns true if this button contains at least one item which is not disabled, or marked as a separator.

Method: is_item_disabled(idx: int) -> bool
Returns true if the item at index idx is disabled.

Method: is_item_separator(idx: int) -> bool
Returns true if the item at index idx is marked as a separator.

Method: is_search_bar_enabled() -> bool
Returns true if the search bar is enabled.

Method: remove_item(idx: int)
Removes the item at index idx.

Method: select(idx: int)
Selects an item by index and makes it the current item. This will work even if the item is disabled. Passing -1 as the index deselects any currently selected item.

Method: set_disable_shortcuts(disabled: bool)
If true, shortcuts are disabled and cannot be used to trigger the button.

Method: set_item_auto_translate_mode(idx: int, mode: AutoTranslateMode)
Sets the auto translate mode of the item at index idx. Items use Node.AUTO_TRANSLATE_MODE_INHERIT by default, which uses the same auto translate mode as the OptionButton itself.

Method: set_item_disabled(idx: int, disabled: bool)
Sets whether the item at index idx is disabled. Disabled items are drawn differently in the dropdown and are not selectable by the user. If the current selected item is set as disabled, it will remain selected.

Method: set_item_icon(idx: int, texture: Texture2D)
Sets the icon of the item at index idx.

Method: set_item_id(idx: int, id: int)
Sets the ID of the item at index idx.

Method: set_item_metadata(idx: int, metadata: Variant)
Sets the metadata of an item. Metadata may be of any type and can be used to store extra information about an item, such as an external string ID.

Method: set_item_text(idx: int, text: String)
Sets the text of the item at index idx.

Method: set_item_tooltip(idx: int, tooltip: String)
Sets the tooltip of the item at index idx.

Method: show_popup()
Adjusts popup position and sizing for the OptionButton, then shows the PopupMenu. Prefer this over using get_popup().popup().
---CHUNK---
Document: OptionButton
Path: godot/classes/class_optionbutton.rst
Summary: Describes theme properties for the OptionButton class, including arrow margin, modulation, and icon.

Theme Property Descriptions
int arrow_margin = 4: The horizontal space between the arrow icon and the right edge of the button.
int modulate_arrow = 0: If different than 0, the arrow icon will be modulated to the font color.
Texture2D arrow: The arrow icon to be drawn on the right end of the button.